Package: hsical
Title: Hyperspectral Image Calibration Tool
Version: 2.0.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Maurycy", "Żarczyński", , email = "maurycy.zarczynski@ug.edu.pl", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Claude", role = "ctb", comment = "Anthropic; two-mode v2.0 rebuild"))
Description: A Shiny companion for single-core hyperspectral scanning. In
    Calibrate mode it derives the ideal field of view and pixel geometry from
    motor positions and scan dimensions and checks square-pixel aspect ratio
    with a three-tier indicator. In Log mode it records per-capture metadata by
    collecting operator input and ENVI .hdr/.log values into an HSItools
    metadata sidecar, with a Review panel to read sidecars back. hsical owns no
    schema of its own; sidecar structure, serialization, and validation belong
    to HSItools.
